    {
      "sort": 100000,
      "name": "Traveller Creation",
      "type": "text",
      "_id": "vE5oPwBjke2E33MU",
      "system": {},
      "title": {
        "show": true,
        "level": 1
      },
      "image": {},
      "text": {
        "format": 1,
        "content": "<p>Travellers can be created using a <strong>Traveller</strong> type of Actor. An NPC is a simplified Traveller which lacks most of the information around the life path character generation.</p><h2>Rolling Characteristics</h2><p>You can roll characteristics by clicking the dice symbol next to the characteristics on the Traveller sheet. This will roll 2D6 for each characteristic.</p><p>They will automatically calculate the Dice Modifier for that characteristic.</p><p>You can use a <strong>Package</strong> actor to define different characteristic rolls for non-human characters. Set it as a racial package, and define what dice rolls are used for each characteristic. When the Package is dragged onto a <strong>Traveller</strong> or <strong>NPC</strong> sheet, the sheet will remember what dice to roll each time.</p><p>Characteristics supported are: STR, DEX, END, INT, EDU, SOC, CHA, TER, PSI, WLT, LCK, MRL, STY, RES, FOL, REP</p><h2>Background Skills</h2><p>Click the Background Skills tick box to display which skills can be selected as background skills.</p><p>By default, characters are created at 18 years old.</p><p></p><iframe width=\"1036\" height=\"583\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/hOwzflHXzqM?autolay=1&amp;loop=1\"></iframe><p></p>"
      },
