    {
      "sort": 400000,
      "name": "Trade",
      "type": "text",
      "_id": "DHrzw8S7F6Xpq23b",
      "system": {},
      "title": {
        "show": true,
        "level": 1
      },
      "image": {},
      "text": {
        "format": 1,
        "content": "<p>The Traveller trade system is implemented using the World and Spacecraft actors, and the Cargo Item types.</p><p></p><h2>Passengers</h2><p>To generate passengers, you need two or more Worlds defined, each with non-zero populations. They should have different X and Y coordinates as well.</p><p>If you have World A and World B, open both world sheets, and drag the planet icon from World B to World A. On the <strong>Freight</strong> tab on World A, you should see a list of passengers created. This will be the passengers wanting to travel to World B.</p><p>You can then drag the passengers from the world sheet onto a spacecraft sheet. The spacecraft will have cash added to it as the passengers pay for their trip.</p><p>Later, you can drag the passengers from the spacecraft to World B. The passengers will be removed from the spacecraft.</p><p>We do not use the random passenger table in the core rules. Instead, a much more flexible system is used to generate passengers, based on their class.</p><p></p><h4>Missing Features</h4><ul><li><p>There are no modifiers to numbers or types of passengers according to Steward skill, or whether the ship has luxury staterooms.</p></li><li><p>There is no tracking of how many staterooms (or cold berths) are taken up with passengers</p></li><li><p>We don't account for the luggage of High Passengers.</p></li></ul><p></p><h2>Freight</h2><p>Freight is calculated in the same way as for Passengers. Drag the world you are going to, to the world you are currently at. Freight lots will be calculated for that trip, and added to the World sheet.</p><h4>Missing Features</h4><ul><li><p>We don't currently handle Mail.</p></li></ul><p></p><h2>Speculative Trade</h2><p>Speculative trade isn't based on a destination world, so there is only one set of speculative trade goods. These are displayed on the Trade tab of a world.</p><p></p>"
      },
